Usage: gskill <command> [flags]

Reproducible package manager for agentic AI skills.

Flags:
  -h, --help              Show context-sensitive help.
      --json              Emit machine-readable JSON on stdout.
      --quiet             Suppress diagnostics on stderr.
      --no-interactive    Disable prompts and colored output.
      --yes               Assume yes for confirmation prompts.
      --offline           Operate without network access.
      --no-cache          Bypass the content cache.
      --dry-run           Report actions without applying them.
      --config=STRING     Path to a config file.
  -v, --verbose           Enable verbose diagnostics.
  -C, --dir=STRING        Run as if gskill started in this directory.

CORE
  init [flags]
    Initialize local gskill state (.gskill, .agents/skills, gitignore).

  add <source> [flags]
    Add and install a new skill.

  onboard [flags]
    Guided skill installation without a predefined source.

  install [flags]
    Install all declared skills (additive, idempotent).

  update [<skills> ...] [flags]
    Advance skills within their version constraints.

  remove <skills> ... [flags]
    Uninstall skills and clean up.

INSPECT
  list [flags]
    List installed skills, their status, and per-agent health.

  info <name> [flags]
    Show details for one skill.

  search (find) <query> [flags]
    Search for skills in a source, a GitHub owner, or configured repositories.

  outdated [flags]
    Show skills with newer versions available.

PROJECT (lockfile · installed state)
  project <command> [flags]
    Manage this project's lockfile and installed state.

MORE
  source <command> [flags]
    Inspect a skill source (list/inspect/check) without installing.

  cache <command> [flags]
    Manage the content cache.

  config <command> [flags]
    Inspect layered configuration.

  unlink --agent=STRING <skill> [flags]
    Detach one agent from a skill (--prune removes it when the last agent goes).

  doctor [flags]
    Check the environment and declared requirements.

  dashboard (tui) [flags]
    Launch the interactive dashboard.

  completion <shell> [flags]
    Print a shell completion script.

  version [flags]
    Print the gskill version.

Run "gskill <command> --help" for more information on a command.
